On June 16, 2022, the President signed two laws into effect. The first law, H.R. 3579, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 200 East Main Street in Maroa, Illinois, as the Jeremy L. Ridlen Post Office. The second law, H.R. 4168, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 6223 Maple Street in Omaha, Nebraska, as the Petty Officer 1st Class Charles Jackson French Post Office. The President expressed gratitude to Representatives Rodney Davis, Cheri Bustos, Don Bacon, Adrian Smith, and others for their leadership in these matters.